    "## Task 1: Misuse of health data\n",
    "**Example** Google DeepMind and the Royal Free NHS Trust (UK)\n",
    "\n",
    "**What happened?** The Royal Free NHS trust disclosed the details of 1.6 million patients to Google’s health unit, called Google DeepMind, in 2015, in order to build an app to identify acute kidney injury. Patients were not informed that this data would be shared, and the data included more information than required. In 2017, the UK Information Commissioner decided that the agreement would be in violation of data protection legislation.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Ethical issues involved** Lack of informed consent, secondary use of data without transparency, insufficient data minimization, and erosion of trust in healthcare institutions.\n",
    "\n",
    "**What could have been done to prevent it?** Obtain explicit informed consent or provide an opt-out option, data sharing should be restricted to only what is strictly necessary, and increase transparency around the partnership."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b058b988",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 2: Breaches in health data security\n",
    "**Example** Community Health Systems Data Breach (2014)\n",
    "\n",
    "**What happened?** In 2014, the biggest US hospital operator, Community Health Systems (CHS), announced the detection of a serious cybercrime where the data of around 4.5 million of its patients was compromised. The hackers were able to access the data through a weakness in the company’s computer network through the use of malware, leading to the exposure of names, addresses, birth dates, telephone numbers and SSNs.\n",
    "\n",
    "**What could have been done to prevent it?** Improved security controls in the network, such as firewalls, regular vulnerability scanning and patching of software, intrusion detection systems to identify suspicious activity sooner, and multi-factor authentication for restricting unauthorized usage\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3dfd7a22",
